prompt.transcript:
28yo, G1P0, 24+2, BMI 25, Rh+ve
Monochorionic diamniotic twin pregnancy, conceived naturally
Issues:
Concerns regarding growth restriction and potential complications in monochorionic twins
Previous ultrasound scans showed discordant growth

Background:
Fetus 1 estimated weight 630g, Fetus 2 estimated weight 550g, abdominal circumference difference of 12mm
Umbilical artery Doppler and middle cerebral artery Doppler within normal limits for both fetuses
Previous scan on 20th April showed Fetus 1 estimated weight 500g, Fetus 2 estimated weight 420g
G&S tests from 10th May pending

Assessment:
Discordant growth noted, Fetus 2 is smaller, however, umbilical artery Doppler and middle cerebral artery Doppler are within normal limits
Risk of twin-to-twin transfusion syndrome (TTTS) needs to be monitored closely

Discussion:
High-risk obstetric consultant review recommended due to monochorionic diamniotic twin pregnancy
Weekly ultrasound scans to monitor growth and umbilical artery Doppler
Need to counsel patient regarding potential complications, including TTTS and selective fetal growth restriction

Plan:
Weekly ultrasound scans to monitor growth and umbilical artery Doppler
CMW to check results at next ANC appt
Reassure patient regarding close monitoring and potential interventions if needed
Please consider referral to fetal medicine unit for further assessment and management
Telephone ANC in 1/52 if still pregnant
